description._content: This band was playing al fresco. Well, in a tent, really, but that's almost al fresco. Good band, too. I wanted to buy their CD, but it turned out they hadn't been a band long enough to have one.

Pisces balloon sculpture taking shape in the Grand Gallery, National Museum of Scotland. World-renowned, New York based artist Jason Hackenwerth's residency in the National Museum of Scotland created the largest visual spectacle the Science Festival has ever seen. Installed over several days by Jason and his team, see the the as hundreds of balloons were woven together to build this intricate structure. Find out more here about Pisces at Science Festival.

Soylent Green Starring Charlton Heston and Edward G Robinson ,and directed by Richard Fleischer is science fiction classic. Set in 2022, overpopulation and pollution have led Soylent Industries to release foodstuffs created from Plankton. In this event guest augmentologists responded with ideas about algaculture and synthetic biology. LateLab is a collaboration between Edinburgh International Science Festival, New Media Scotland and the University of Edinburgh’s School of Informatics www.sciencefestival.co.uk/whats-on/latelab This event was part of the GastroFest strand, to find out more about these sensational food and drink events visit www.sciencefestival.co.uk/whats-on/gastrofest Photography by Chris Scott, www.flickr.com/photos/chrisdonia
